body:
So apparently my blood pressure is on the low end of average (mid-90s over 60 I think? I don’t know what that means), which is apparently why I crave salt so much especially after exercise. I need the electrolytes.

Downside is I have to not have large meals. No gorging on half a pizza and breadsticks even if I have the calorie space. Only a moderate 2 slices and 1 breadstick for Glee. :(

At least my heart and lungs are clear.

summary: As expected, I feel like I’m losing a lot of the “holiday weight” pretty quickly. I was around 268 before December. It’s nice to...
body:
12.28.18 - 171.8 (-3.8)

As expected, I feel like I’m losing a lot of the “holiday weight” pretty quickly. I was around 268 before December. It’s nice to see that it is coming right back off, especially with the whole PCOS and my past with losing weight…Anywho, today I wanted to tell you about the app I use to track my water, Plant Nanny:


I really love Plant Nanny because I think it is so cute. So the concept is that you get this plant. As you drink water throughout the day, you also “water” your plant by choosing the fluid oz you drank. It calculates how much you and your plant need by your weight/activity. You have your choice of different plants and flower pots and backgrounds. The plants are also different difficulties; easy won’t die as easily if you aren’t reaching your full goals, whereas the difficult ones you need to be much more diligent. If you don’t drink enough water 1 day you’ll see the water 💧 by the plant (as you can see, because I didn’t do a good job of staying hydrated yesterday!) On the second day it will warn you that your plant will die, and on the third day it dies. You have the option to bring it back to life or start over (if you have water if life). The plants also grow through levels.


The one negative thing I have heard about it, which doesn’t bother me, is sometimes the ounces are off? So you may put in 16 oz but it will say you drank 14. It’s never by a ton, so this doesn’t really bother me. I am trying to drink more, anyway! But if this is something that might bother you, just be prepared.


So that’s it for today, kiddos! Yesterday was a better day for me eating wise, and today my goal is to make my plant happy again. 😂 Hope you all have a fantastic Friday!

summary: Getting from very unfit to fit via /r/Fitness
title: Getting from very unfit to fit via /r/Fitness
body:
Ok so I’m in my mid 30s, overweight and very unfit. My New Year goal isn’t about weight loss it’s about getting fit. I get out of breath climbing the stairs, so like most people this time of year I’m joining the gym.

But my question is - where to start? I doubt I could jog any longer than 60s, so i was I thinking do I start off doing fast paced uphill walks on the treadmill to get some level of base fitness going before attempting a jog and other cardio exercises?

I want to get fit, but don’t want to overdo the first few sessions but at the same time I don’t want to waste my time by not doing enough. Suggestions?

via reddit http://bit.ly/2Roks04

caption:
Flex 💪 Friday come back to mama 🙄😂🤦🏻‍♀️

Suns ☀️ out guns 💪 out will be here before I know it.

For me, it’s an overall healthier lifestyle not something I do once and a while.

With that being said… this fall I did get a tad bit off track on food and fitness. 🍕🍟🍪 We all have excuses and it’s sometimes easier to be lazier. When I’m stressed I don’t always make the best choices 🍕. Time to refocus and let all those challenges go.
